<a class="definition-word" data-category="general-biology" id="crispr_cas9">CRISPR Cas9</a> - A new tool based on the bacterial CRISPR-Cas system to target and cut <a href="#dna_desoxyribonucleic_acid">DNA</a>, thus allowing for targeted <a href="#genome">genome</a> editing. CRISPR stands for clustered regularly interspaced short palindromic repeats.